.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:2:name: deep-agent-improvement
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:3:description: "Evaluator-first bounded agent improvement: 5-dim scoring, dynamic profiling, packet-local candidates, guarded promotion."
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:7:  - deep-agent-improvement
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:13:  - model-benchmark mode
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:14:  - benchmark a model or prompt framework
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:17:<!-- Keywords: deep-agent-improvement, deep-agent-improvement, agent-improvement, benchmark-harness, score-candidate, promote-candidate, rollback-candidate -->
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:21:Evaluator-first workflow for testing whether a bounded agent surface can be improved without immediately mutating the source of truth. It combines packet-local candidates, deterministic scoring, repeatable benchmarks, and explicit promotion or rollback gates.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:27:### Two Co-Equal Lanes
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:29:This skill supports two co-equal use-case lanes that share the same candidate, dispatcher, and scorer seams:
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:31:| Lane | Pick when | Command |
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:33:| **Lane A: Agent-Improvement** | You want to improve a bounded agent `.md` file | `/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop` |
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:34:| **Lane B: Model-Benchmark** | You want to benchmark a model or prompt framework | `/deep:start-model-benchmark-loop` |
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:36:Lane A is detailed in §3 (Runtime Initialization, Proposal and Evaluation, Promotion and Recovery). Lane B is detailed in §4. Both lanes run the same loop shape and keep the agent-improvement path byte-identical when no mode flag is set.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:41:- You want to test whether an agent prompt or instruction surface can be improved (Lane A)
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:42:- You want to benchmark a model or prompt framework against repeatable fixtures (Lane B)
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:45:- You need target-specific benchmark or scoring rules before any canonical mutation
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:52:Use this skill to set up a proposal-first loop for any bounded agent file, write packet-local candidates, and record append-only evidence.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:56:Use this skill when candidate quality must be judged by produced artifacts and repeatability reports, not just by how a prompt file reads in isolation.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:64:Use Lane B (model-benchmark) when the thing under test is a model or prompt framework rather than an agent definition. It runs the same loop shape against a benchmark profile and scores produced outputs, sharing the candidate, dispatcher, and scorer seams with the agent-improvement path. See §4 below.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:70:- Direct canonical edits without a packet-local candidate and evaluator evidence
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:71:- Broad runtime-mirror synchronization work presented as benchmark truth
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:85:- `scripts/` for deterministic benchmark, scoring, reduction, promotion, rollback, and drift-check helpers
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:87:**Lane awareness**: resources are organized by lane. `references/agent-improvement/` and `assets/agent-improvement/` carry Lane A guidance, while `references/model-benchmark/` and `assets/model-benchmark/` carry Lane B guidance. `RESOURCE_MAP` routes the `MODEL_BENCHMARK` intent to the Lane B references, and `RUNTIME_ASSETS` loads the Lane B benchmark profile only when the `MODEL_BENCHMARK` intent is selected. The `ALWAYS` and shared `references/shared/` resources apply to both lanes.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:93:| ALWAYS | Every skill invocation | `references/shared/quick_reference.md` |
