.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/validation_baselines.md:21:Captures `advisor_validate` baseline metrics and the troubleshooting playbook for validation slice regressions.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/validation_baselines.md:50:| Python regression suite | full pass | `mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor_regression.py` |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/validation_baselines.md:57:Drift threshold: top-1 accuracy below 80.5% on full corpus OR below 77.5% on holdout is a hard regression that blocks ship.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/validation_baselines.md:96:Drift signal: a drop of more than 2 percentage points. Likely causes are scorer weight changes, new skills disrupting the lexical lane or stale skill metadata.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/validation_baselines.md:102:Drift signal: drop > 1pp is a stronger regression signal than the corpus slice because holdout is unseen during weight tuning.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/validation_baselines.md:128:| Corpus top-1 drops > 2pp | Scorer weight change OR new skill metadata regression | Run `advisor_rebuild --force`. If still regressed, inspect `perSkill[]` for the regressed skills. Roll back weights per `lane_weight_tuning.md` §6 |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/validation_baselines.md:130:| UNKNOWN count spikes above 10 | Trust-state went to `absent` OR scorer threshold misconfigured | Check `advisor_status.trustState`. If `absent`, run `advisor_rebuild`. If `live`, inspect lane weights for an over-aggressive threshold |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/validation_baselines.md:134:| Uncached p95 > 25 ms | Scoring algorithm changed OR semantic_shadow lane embedding lookup slow | Profile via `mcp_server/bench/`. If semantic_shadow is the culprit, verify embeddings index freshness |
